cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper is about neural language models (NLMs) and their tradeoff between accuracy and efficiency, specifically in the context of mobile devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as pruning and quasi-recurrent neural networks, which suggest categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates energy consumption, which could fall under categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
